description.displayText:
We have been so lucky to have the opportunity to work with Paula.

Paula stepped in to help us for a  short term opportunity and has now looked after our 7.5 month son for ~2 months. 

Paula is everything you would dream of. She will play and care for your baby, read to them books, take them out, organize play dates, pay attention to their development needs, and work with you to discuss what you should be thinking about next. She is experienced with babies and has the confidence to navigate the fun and the challenging days. She was happy to come in early or stay late when asked. Despite this being a short term appointment, she looked after our son with a lot of care and attention and they have become very close. I spend the afternoons listening to them giggle whilst they play. As a first time mom, I never worry when I leave the house as I know that my baby is in great hands! If our circumstances were different i would 100% work with Paula full time. Any family who gets to work with her will be very lucky! 


We are also working remotely and it has been very nice to have her in the apartment, spend time together and learn from her. 

Highly recommend and would work with Paula again and again!

description.displayText:
Paula was simply amazing and I'd hire her again (and have) in a heartbeat! 

We went through 5+ full-time nannies in 2 months due to cancellations, delays, sickness, vacations and she was the last and best of them all. Paula cared for our 1 1/2 year old. 

She was attentive, timely, responsive, and blended in with my family really well. My parents got along with her when they visited (they don't get along with everyone). She was helpful in cleaning/tidying up and did things proactively without me asking. We trusted her through COVID - she was upfront about information (e.g. when she attended her best friend's wedding) and willingly tested. 

Most of all, my child loved her and bonded quickly!!! When I was working from home - I could hear the giggles, little feet running, I could hear Paula's patience, and when she left/came my child would run up and give the biggest smile and hug.

Sad that Paula is moving to NY, but know she will make some family happy!

description.displayText: What a delight! It was truly wonderful having Paula care for my son for a week as I returned to work. She is kind, relaxed, and has an instantly calming presence. My son loved her immediately. Having Paula at home to play with my son made my return to work so much easier because I knew he was being well cared-for.

description.displayText: Wow. Paula was incredible. I had to travel to San Francisco for two weeks for work and wasn't ready to leave my 8 month old for that long so we brought him with and hired Paula to watch him while I was at work during the day. Paula was the first person outside of family that watched our son and she made us feel completely confident and happy about it. She was very professional, courteous and easy-going and our son had a great time with her. She was very engaged with him the whole time, and she followed our schedule seamlessly. Only wish we could have her as our nanny back home. Hire her- you won't regret it!

description.displayText: Paula is a very attentive and thorough sitter. We used to do play dates together and she always has great ideas to keep the kids busy and having a great time! She is responsible, detail oriented and a very kind person.

description.displayText: Paula babysat my twin girls several times when they were four and five years old. She is incredibly loving and always coming up with fun activities for the kids to do. She has tons of energy so she can really keep up with them and tire them out before bedtime. She always kept them engaged with stories, songs and games. She was always very punctual and professional and followed any instructions I gave her perfectly. When she moved out of the area we all missed her a lot, and know that any future families she works with are very lucky.

description.displayText: Paula is amazing! She was recommended to me by a colleague. She is one of the few people I can trust with my son. She has taken care of my son on and off  since he was a few months old till 2.5 years old. 5 stars.  Highly recommend. She is: patient, understanding, responsible, respectful, honest, caring, and a person of integrity. Her knowledge of childhood development was such a resource to me and my family. We all felt as if she was caring for my child as if he was her very own. Paula has been such a blessing to us and i am certain she will be a blessing to your family.
